Data Cleaning

The source dataset contained several data quality issues that were addressed during the ETL process.

Cleaning activities performed
Standardized inconsistent school names.
Corrected inconsistent county, region, sub-county, and country values.
Standardized teacher gender values.
Standardized subject names and teacher specialties.
Standardized learning modes, scholarship status, assessment types, and academic terms.
Corrected invalid and mixed-format date values.
Filled missing identifiers where they could be confidently inferred from existing records.
Removed duplicate records from dimension tables.
Standardized capitalization across descriptive fields.
Data Modeling

The original flat dataset was normalized into a dimensional model consisting of one fact table and multiple dimension tables.

Fact Table
FactPerformance
Dimension Tables
DimStudent
DimTeacher
DimSchool
DimSubject

Relationships were configured using:

One-to-Many Cardinality
Single Cross Filter Direction
Primary and Foreign Keys
Star Schema Design

This model improves report performance, reduces redundancy, and simplifies analytical queries.

