Assumptions & Business Rules

Several assumptions were required because the source dataset contained missing or ambiguous information.

Pass Mark

The dataset did not specify an official pass mark. A pass mark of 50% was assumed and used consistently when calculating:

Pass Rate
Failure Rate
Students Below Pass Mark
Schools Requiring Academic Support
Duplicate Teacher Records

Some teacher records contained duplicate entries where the teacher had the same name and taught the same subject but appeared with multiple records. After investigation, these were treated as duplicate records and assigned a single teacher identifier to maintain data integrity within the dimensional model.

Revenue Analysis

The dataset did not contain fields representing actual revenue collected or fee payments. As a result, the financial analysis focuses on outstanding fee balances rather than revenue generated by schools. Visuals and measures were designed to reflect this limitation accurately.
